OL,3,CThe zero-carbon homes where energy
OL,4,Cbills are #100 a year
OL,6,FResidents generate their own water and
OL,7,Ffood supplies. Wind turbines and a
OL,8,Fsolar photovoltaic system provide most
OL,9,Fof the energy required to run their
OL,10,Fhomes.
OL,12,FTemperatures inside each one are
OL,13,Fmaintained at 18-23C 24 hours a day,
OL,14,Fyear-round.
OL,16,FYet, while the average UK energy bill
OL,17,Fis around #1,570 a year, here the
OL,18,Fresidents can pay as little as #100.
