OL,3,CThe zero-carbon homes where energy
OL,4,Cbills are #100 a year
OL,6,FDeborah Yates, who has lived on the
OL,7,Fdevelopment for more than ten years,
OL,8,Fsaid the design of the homes meant
OL,9,Fbody heat was absorbed into the
OL,10,Fconcrete walls and slowly released
OL,11,Fthroughout the day. Guests are welcome.
OL,13,F"We get tours of 16 or 17 students in
OL,14,Fthe winter I am like 'come on in!'"
OL,15,Fshe said.
OL,17,F"My last energy bill was #52 pounds
OL,18,Ffor three months.
